---
import { weather } from "../../lib/practical-info-data";
---

<section class="weather-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Weather & Climate</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">What to expect at our elevation</p>

    <div class="weather-grid">
      {weather.map((item) => (
        <div class="weather-card">
          <div class="weather-emoji">{item.emoji}</div>
          <h3>{item.season}</h3>
          <div class="weather-temp">{item.temperature}</div>
          <p>{item.description}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="climate-info">
      <h3>Climate Characteristics</h3>
      
      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-item">
          <h4>📍 Elevation</h4>
          <p>Salinas sits at 1,350-1,600 meters (4,430-5,250 feet), providing a temperate mountain climate.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-item">
          <h4>🌧️ Rainfall Patterns</h4>
          <p>Rain is common but usually brief afternoon showers. Mornings are typically clear and perfect for activities. Waterproof jacket recommended.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-item">
          <h4>☀️ UV Intensity</h4>
          <p>At this altitude, UV exposure is intense even on cloudy days. High SPF sunscreen (50+) and protective clothing essential.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-item">
          <h4>🌬️ Wind & Air Quality</h4>
          <p>Winds are generally light to moderate. Air quality is excellent with minimal pollution thanks to Ecuador's mountainous terrain and green landscapes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .weather-section {
    padding: 4rem 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f5f5f5 0%, #ffffff 100%);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2D5016;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    color: #666;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
  }

  .weather-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .weather-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    transition: all 300ms ease;
  }

  .weather-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: #2D5016;
  }

  .weather-emoji {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .weather-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: #2D5016;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .weather-temp {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #8B7355;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .weather-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #666;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .climate-info {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  .climate-info h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #2D5016;
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
  }

  .info-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .info-item h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #2D5016;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .info-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .weather-section {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .weather-grid {
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .weather-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .climate-info {
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .info-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
